From: Lee Jones <lee@kernel.org>
Date: Fri, 25 Nov 2022 12:07:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Kconfig.debug: provide a little extra FRAME_WARN leeway when
 KASAN is enabled
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 6.0.12
Git-commit: 152fe65f300e1819d59b80477d3e0999b4d5d7d2

commit 152fe65f300e1819d59b80477d3e0999b4d5d7d2 upstream.

When enabled, KASAN enlarges function's stack-frames.  Pushing quite a few
over the current threshold.  This can mainly be seen on 32-bit
architectures where the present limit (when !GCC) is a lowly 1024-Bytes.

